<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-582-474  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 582 474.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 8 1989 v3 n29 p50(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Automate creation of bilingual glossaries. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   glps Products (product introduction).andO;Product:   Vocabulary Creator DL (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionForeign LanguagesRussian LanguageAlphabets.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Automate creation of bilingual glossariesandM;Chapel Hill, N.C.andP;  -- Extending its line of products aimed at educators,students and translators who use Cyrillic and other non-Latin character sets,glps Products recently released an application that automates the creation ofworld lists and dual-language vocabularies.andM;The company's name stands for generic language processing system, andVocabulary Creator DL (dual language) is a line-oriented multiwindow texteditor with special features for mixed-language work.andP;  Used with glps' AbtopIII &quot;language support package,&quot; it can distinguish Russian and English words,then generate and sort vocabularies -- especially formatted word lists --that correctly handle Cyrillic diacritical marks and capitalization.andM;Vocabularies can be searched by stem, so that the proper root word is locateddespite variations in gramatical form.andP;  The program also offers a variety ofcommands for filtering, subdividing and updating vocabularies.andM;Users can turn the lists into full-blown glossaries, complete withdefinitions grammatical information and references to textbooks or literarysources.andP;  glps markets a 5,500-word Russian-English glossary, which buyerscan use as the foundation for building custom glossaries with up to 32,700entries.andM;Vocabulary Creator DL costs $74.95, or $59.95 for students.andP;  The glps RussianWord List, including keys to eight leading textbooks, is priced at $39.95($29.95 for students).andM;Another version of the program, called Vocabulary Creator SL (singleversion), can be used with any language written in standard Mac fonts.andP;  Itwill be released this month.andM;glps can be reached at P.O Box 3454, Chapel Hill, N.C.andP;  27515; (919)933-6530.andO;</TEXT></DOC>